top-level class : not enclosed in code block of another class (public or none)
Access Modifiers :
    public - any class in any package
    private - no other class
    protected - same package class, subclasses in other packages
    default -classes in same package

Encapsulation: bundling of behaviour/attributes on a single object
               hiding fields from public access

Class properties needs to have an access modifier
null - attribute has a type but no refernce to an object
getter - method/class that retrieves the value of a private field and returns it.
setter - method/class that sets the value of a private field.

this - refers to the instance that was created when the object was instantiated.


